Kaizer Chiefs announced a new partnership with Medshield Medical Scheme on Thursday.The deal with medical aid company Medshield was announced by Chiefs' chairman Kaizer Motaung at the club's headquarters in Naturena Johannesburg."This is a very important exercise for us because we carry a lot of costs making sure our team are in top shape " Motaung said."We also have to ensure the health of our technical staff. We also have our supporters whose interests we have at heart."Chiefs' marketing director Jessica Motaung said options are being explored as to how the deal can benefit supporters. Medshield have been in the business of medical insurance since 1968. - TMG Digital/TMG Sport